# ===== BACKEND ENVIRONMENT CONFIGURATION =====
# Environment variables are now managed in the root-level .env file
# Copy the root .env.example to .env in the project root and configure there

# This file is kept for reference but the actual configuration
# should be done in the main .env file at the project root level.

# Key variables needed for backend:
# - GOOGLE_MAPS_API_KEY (required)
# - OPENAI_API_KEY (optional)
# - PORT (default: 3001)
# - NODE_ENV (default: development)
# - FRONTEND_URL (for CORS)
# - JWT_SECRET (required for CRM)

# All backend services will read from the root-level .env file